<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1646,1887]" pageId="10" pageNumber="531">
Some specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[443,722,1754,1779]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="531" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variegata">
<emphasis box="[443,722,1754,1779]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="531">Physocephala variegata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can have a completely orange-brown abdomen, completely orange pleura and a scutum that is barely darkened in the centre only. These specimens agree completely with the description of 
<taxonomicName box="[322,407,1826,1851]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="531" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laeta">
<emphasis box="[322,407,1826,1851]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="531">P. laeta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis box="[428,513,1826,1851]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="531">P. l ae t a</emphasis>
is therefore interpreted as a pale colour colour morph of 
<taxonomicName box="[1207,1346,1828,1851]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="531" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variegata">
<emphasis box="[1207,1346,1828,1851]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="531">P. variegata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and is accordingly treated as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[637,771,1863,1886]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="531" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variegata">
<emphasis box="[637,771,1863,1886]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="531">P. variegata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
